ResNet-50 is an already trained deep learning model on the CNN architecture for processing visual input. The ResNet-50 model has a total of 50 layers. This model was trained with one million photographs from the ImageNet database, which has 1000 categories of objects. ResNet50 is a bit different from other pre-trained models such as AlexNet, GoogleNet, and VGG19, due to its great generalization ability and minimum error rates in recognition tests. The system will work on the exact classification of photos into 1000 categories, including keyboards, mice, pencils, and animals, using a 224 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
